{
  "question_id": "a7d21436-d0d5-4911-802e-18071aade530",
  "short_text": "Hollow Square",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print a **Square** of `N` rows using stars (`*`).\r\n\r\n```\r\n* * * * * * \r\n*         * \r\n*         * \r\n*         * \r\n*         * \r\n* * * * * * \r\n```\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nThere is a space after every star (`*`).\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `N` rows containing stars (`*`) as a **Square** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`,\r\n\r\n- Print stars (`*`) on **4** rows as shown in the given image.\r\n  - The first row contains **4** stars (`*`).\r\n  - The middle **2** rows contain **2** stars (`*`).\r\n  - The last row contains **4** stars (`*`).\r\n\r\n    <Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-hollow-square.png' widthPercent='50'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nIn the given image, \r\n\r\n- The Empty box indicates two spaces (\"&nbsp;&nbsp;\").\r\n- The Star in the box indicates star and a space (\"* \").\r\n\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\nThe output should be,\r\n\r\n```\r\n* * * * \r\n*     * \r\n*     * \r\n* * * *\r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "6a87d855-d545-4b23-b492-90705220b794",
      "code_content": "n = int(input())\n\nprint(\"* \" * n)\n\nfor i in range(1, n - 1):\n    middle_spaces = \"  \" * (n - 2)\n    row = \"* \" + middle_spaces + \"* \"\n    print(row)\n    \nprint(\"* \" * n)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
